          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Your app can manage an input/output command queueâ€™s scratch memory by an implementing ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLIOScratchBufferAllocator",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " in one of your types, and assigning an instance of it to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLIOCommandQueueDescriptor/scratchBufferAllocator",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". Otherwise, set to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "nil",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to instruct the input/output command queue to allocate and manage its own scratch buffers.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "An input/output command queue uses scratch buffers for memory-intensives tasks, including loading textures and decompressing asset files.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
